xccdf:description.xhtml:p:
When obtaining and installing software packages (typically via                                   yum


), it's imperative that packages are sourced only from valid and authorized repositories. For PostgreSQL, a short list of valid repositories would include CentOS (                                  www.centos.org


) and the official PostgreSQL website (                                  yum.postgresql.org


).

xhtml:p.xhtml:p:
                              Note:


 In this example, a new logfile will be created for each day (e.g.                                                     postgresql-20180901.log


)

xhtml:p.xhtml:code:
SELECT proname, proacl FROM pg_proc WHERE proname = 'delete_customer';
proname | proacl
-----------------+--------------------------------------------------------
delete_customer | {=X/postgres,postgres=X/postgres,appwriter=X/postgres}
(1 row)

